    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate)\u00a0<strong>half</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[all]</span> the<strong> garlic</strong></p> <p>Chop the <strong>capers</strong> roughly</p> <p>\u00a0</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-smoked-mackerel-caesar-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>mayonnaise</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!), <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>chopped capers</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong></p> <p>Add<strong> half</strong> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>caesar dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-smoked-mackerel-caesar-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear the <strong>outer leaves</strong> from the <strong>little gem lettuces</strong></p> <p>Shred the<strong> inner cores </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-smoked-mackerel-caesar-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rip the<strong> ciabatta\u00a0roll<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p> <p>Add the <strong>ripped ciabatta</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until golden and crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>golden</strong>\u00a0<strong>croutons</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-smoked-mackerel-caesar-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the skin from the <strong>smoked mackerel fillets</strong></p> <p>Tear the <strong>mackerel</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p> <p>Add the<strong> torn mackerel</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>cornflour</strong> and give it a gentle mix up until the mackerel is fully coated</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-smoked-mackerel-caesar-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0over a high heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated mackerel</strong> and cook for 3-4 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp</p> <p>Tip: Don't turn the mackerel too often, as this will stop it from crisping!</p> <p>Once done, transfer the<strong> crispy mackerel</strong> to <strong>kitchen paper</strong> and set aside</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-smoked-mackerel-caesar-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>caesar dressing</strong> (save the rest for later!)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-smoked-mackerel-caesar-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> little gem leaves</strong> in bowls topped with the <strong>dressed lettuce</strong>, <strong>golden croutons</strong> and <strong>remaining grated cheese</strong></p> <p>Top with the <strong>crispy mackerel</strong> and drizzle the<strong> remaining dressing</strong> all over</p> <p>Season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
